Technique: DOVETAIL (JOINT); WRITTEN WITH A REED PEN/REED WITH SPLIT NIB
Name: Greek papyrus
Description: This tiny, but precious fragment, which comes from the town of Oxyrhynchus (P.Oxy. XIII 1613) and which dates from the 2nd century of our era, contains a list of athenian rulers of the Archaic Period mentioning their number of years of service.
